This paper deals with the design of a low-overhead approach for memory access obfuscation, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the privacy guarantees of the proposed approach, which falls under the category of database security (cs.DB) and cryptography (cs.CY). Finally, the paper presents theoretical analysis and simulations, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG).
